Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title set

chapter set-title

Purpose:
  Rename an existing chapter in the archive TOC.

Usage:
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title set --title <title> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  wikigraph <chapter-uri>/title set --clear [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Behavior:
  - Updates only the chapter title stored in the TOC.
  - Does not change source text, graph nodes, summaries, or metadata.
  - `--title <title>` sets the explicit title.
  - `--clear` removes the explicit title and shows `[untitled]`.
  - `--title` and `--clear` are mutually exclusive.
  - Does not call an LLM provider.

Output shape:
  Prints the updated chapter object.

Examples:
  wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/12/title set --title "New Chapter Title"
  wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/12/title set --clear

See also:
  - wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter list --help
  - wikigraph wkg://book.sdpub/chapter/12/state get --help
  - wikigraph help command
